> I have completed the initial analysis and POC for migrating Crystal 
> Reports to FastReport for the PO Requisition module. The FastReport 
> file is attached.
> Below is a concise update with key observations and recommendations.
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
>
>       Key Findings
>
> *1. No Direct Conversion Available*
>
>  *
>
>     There is no reliable or production-ready direct conversion from
>     |.rpt| to |.frx|.
>
>  *
>
>     Current approach followed:
>
>      o
>
>         |.rpt → XML → .frx |
>
>  *
>
>     Output is not pixel-perfect and requires manual rework—especially
>     around layout alignment, grouping, and formatting.
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
> *2. Paid Version – Import Plugin (To Be Verified)*
>
>  *
>
>     FastReport Paid version offers a Crystal Reports import plugin
>     which may support |.rpt → .frx|.
>
>  *
>
>     However:
>
>      o
>
>         This has not been validated yet in our setup.
>
>      o
>
>         Based on available references, the conversion is partial and
>         still needs manual corrections.
>
>  *
>
>     A small POC is required before considering this as a viable path.
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
> *3. Effort & Time Impact*
>
>  *
>
>     Each report needs manual redesign and fine-tuning.
>
>  *
>
>     Pixel-perfect reports (invoices, financial formats) will take
>     significantly more effort due to rendering and layout differences.
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
> *4. Free Version Limitations*
>
>  *
>
>     No Excel (XLSX) export
>
>  *
>
>     No CSV export
>
>  *
>
>     Limited PDF capabilities (no encryption/signing)
>
>  *
>
>     No end-user report designer
>
>  *
>
>     No scheduling or automation support
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
> *5. Current Workaround*
>
>  *
>
>     For Excel/CSV requirements:
>
>      o
>
>         Using *EPPlus (Free)* for generating structured outputs
>
>  *
>
>     This gives better control and avoids layout-based export limitations.
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
>
>       FastReport Paid Version – Overview
>
> Plan 	Cost (Approx) 	Key Features
> Standard 	~$499 / dev / year 	Desktop designer, basic exports
> Professional 	~$599 / dev / year 	Source code, extended features
> Enterprise 	~$799 / dev / year 	Online designer, report server, 
> multi-tenant
> Ultimate 	~$1499 / dev / year 	Full suite with integrations
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
>
>       Benefits of Paid Version
>
>  *
>
>     Advanced Excel export (structured XLSX)
>
>  *
>
>     High-quality PDF (encryption, digital signing)
>
>  *
>
>     Better designer experience (faster development)
>
>  *
>
>     Online report designer (Enterprise)
>
>  *
>
>     Built-in scheduling & report server
>
>  *
>
>     Improved performance for large datasets
>
>  *
>
>     Vendor support for faster issue resolution
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
>
>       Summary
>
>  *
>
>     Migration is not automated and requires manual effort per report
>
>  *
>
>     Free version has functional gaps impacting export and scalability
>
>  *
>
>     Paid version improves capabilities but does not guarantee full
>     conversion
>
>  *
>
>     Import plugin needs validation before making a decision
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
>
>       Recommendation
