      <p>Hi Sir,</p>
      <p>I have completed the initial analysis and POC for migrating
        Crystal Reports to FastReport for the PO Requisition module. The
        FastReport file is attached. <br>
        Below is a concise update with key observations and
        recommendations.</p>
      <hr>
      <h3>Key Findings</h3>
      <p><strong>1. No Direct Conversion Available</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>There is no reliable or production-ready direct conversion
            from <code>.rpt</code> to <code>.frx</code>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Current approach followed:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p><code>.rpt → XML → .frx </code></p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Output is not pixel-perfect and requires manual
            rework—especially around layout alignment, grouping, and
            formatting.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <p><strong>2. Paid Version – Import Plugin (To Be Verified)</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>FastReport Paid version offers a Crystal Reports import
            plugin which may support <code>.rpt → .frx</code>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>However:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>This has not been validated yet in our setup.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>Based on available references, the conversion is
                partial and still needs manual corrections.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>A small POC is required before considering this as a viable
            path.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <p><strong>3. Effort &amp; Time Impact</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>Each report needs manual redesign and fine-tuning.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Pixel-perfect reports (invoices, financial formats) will
            take significantly more effort due to rendering and layout
            differences.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <p><strong>4. Free Version Limitations</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>No Excel (XLSX) export</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>No CSV export</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Limited PDF capabilities (no encryption/signing)</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>No end-user report designer</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>No scheduling or automation support</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <p><strong>5. Current Workaround</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>For Excel/CSV requirements:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>Using <strong>EPPlus (Free)</strong> for generating
                structured outputs</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>This gives better control and avoids layout-based export
            limitations.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <h3>FastReport Paid Version – Overview</h3>
      <table>
        <thead><tr>
            <th>Plan</th>
            <th>Cost (Approx)</th>
            <th>Key Features</th>
          </tr>
        </thead><tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Standard</td>
            <td>~$499 / dev / year</td>
            <td>Desktop designer, basic exports</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Professional</td>
            <td>~$599 / dev / year</td>
            <td>Source code, extended features</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Enterprise</td>
            <td>~$799 / dev / year</td>
            <td>Online designer, report server, multi-tenant</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Ultimate</td>
            <td>~$1499 / dev / year</td>
            <td>Full suite with integrations</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <hr>
      <h3>Benefits of Paid Version</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>Advanced Excel export (structured XLSX)</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>High-quality PDF (encryption, digital signing)</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Better designer experience (faster development)</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Online report designer (Enterprise)</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Built-in scheduling &amp; report server</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Improved performance for large datasets</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Vendor support for faster issue resolution</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <h3>Summary</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>Migration is not automated and requires manual effort per
            report</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Free version has functional gaps impacting export and
            scalability</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Paid version improves capabilities but does not guarantee
            full conversion</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Import plugin needs validation before making a decision</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <h3>Recommendation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>Continue with the current approach (manual conversion +
            refinement)</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Parallelly run a <strong>POC on the Paid version import
              plugin</strong></p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Continue using <strong>EPPlus for Excel export</strong> as
            a stable workaround</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <hr>
      <p>Please let me know how you’d like to proceed, and I can plan
        the next steps accordingly.</p>
